OL,3,CEnd of working from home? Your rights
OL,4,Cto flexible working explained
OL,6,FMs Baxter advised that in any
OL,7,Fpotential dispute, the more
OL,8,F"conversation and discussion" that an
OL,9,Femployee can have with an employer the
OL,10,Fbetter.
OL,12,FShe added: "There is a massive
OL,13,Fdifference in the sort of likelihood
OL,14,Fof succeeding in a flexible working
OL,15,Frequest which just says 'this is what
OL,16,FI want to do' as compared to one that
OL,17,Fsays 'this is what I want to do, this
OL,18,Fis how I think it might affect the
OL,19,Fbusiness, but this is how I think we
OL,20,Fcan address that'.
