OL,3,CEnd of working from home? Your rights
OL,4,Cto flexible working explained
OL,6,F"A request which shows that the
OL,7,Femployee thought about it from the
OL,8,Fcompany's perspective from the off,
OL,9,Fit's much harder to say no to those
OL,10,Fsorts of requests."
OL,12,FWhat does a 'reasonable manner' mean?
OL,14,FMs Baxter said a reasonable manner
OL,15,Fcould be reduced to an employer
OL,16,Fdealing with a request in "good faith,
OL,17,Fbeing honest about the reasons (and)
OL,18,Fnot giving a misleading response as to
OL,19,Fwhy something has or hasn't been
OL,20,Fagreed, and progressing it without an
OL,21,Funreasonable delay".
